Amanda Khoza, News24Ahmed Kathrada (Mlungisi Louw, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; ANC struggle veteran Ahmed Kathrada's condition following an operation remains unchanged.On Monday, Ahmed Kathrada Foundation spokesperson Neeshen Balton said he saw the 87-year-old on Sunday night and he appeared to have had a restful night on Saturday."There aren't significant signs of improvement, he is still being kept sedated but his doctors are happy with his recovery," said Balton.He said contrary to reports, Kathrada is not on life support."His condition remains unchanged and that is a good thing because his condition is stabilising."Kathrada was hospitalised on March 4 for surgery related to blood clotting on the brain.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.